I

IDEAL_FITNESS - Static variable in class sudokuGame.Individual
This is the ideal fitness mean that the player reach the solution, in other words, there are 0 empty cells that don't contain a number, in the sudoku board.
Individual - Class in sudokuGame
Individual abstract class is representing one player (individual), set of genes, that trying to solve the gaven sudoku board, the program will end if one individual success to solve the sudoku board, and if NO one success to solve the sudoku then we use evolutionary algorithm (next generation) method to create new generation of individuals that trying to solve the sudoku.
Individual(int) - Constructor for class sudokuGame.Individual
Initialize Individual instance, the instance will try to solve the sudoku, in GP way.
individuals - Variable in class sudokuGame.Population
Represent a collection of players (individuals) that will try to solve the sudoku board
initializeGradeboard() - Method in class sudokuGame.BoardIndividual
Find which numbers can inserted in every cell without conflict, with the solved cells, and saves these number in gradeboard.
isForward() - Method in class sudokuGame.BoardIndividual
Check if we still can solve more cells without conflict, return true if we can forward solving, false otherwise.
isIdeal() - Method in class sudokuGame.Individual
Ideal individual is the individual that succeed to solve the sudoku, in other words the ideal individual is the one who remain zero empty cell until he solve the sudoku board, so here check if the individual succeed to solve sudoku.
isPrimitive() - Method in class sudokuGame.TerminalOrPrimitive
Check if the type of the instance is Primitive.
isTerminal() - Method in class sudokuGame.TerminalOrPrimitive
Check if the type of the instance is Terminal.
